The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, January 08, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, Jan. 7: The inter-ministerial group for divestment of 10 per cent equity in cash-rich Oil and Natural Gas Corporation has ruled out a split in the companys shares when its public issue hits the market on March 2. Deciding against splitting the shares into smaller denominations, the group instead decided to reduce the lot of shares on offer from 100 to 10. Bidding under the book building route will open on March 2 for seven working days.																								 New Delhi, Jan. 7: Direct tax collection rose by about 23 per cent to Rs 64,230 crore in April-December 2003 mainly due to an impressive mop up from the corporate sector. With this, the Centre has met over 67 per cent of the budgeted Rs 95,569 crore for the 2003-04 fiscal.																								 New Delhi, Jan. 7: The department of income tax has picked Ernst amp; Young and NSE.IT, the IT subsidiary of the National Stock Exchange, as technology advisers for its initiative to provide online facilities to all taxpayers under the Taxnet scheme.																								 New Delhi, Jan. 7: State oil refiners Indian Oil Corporation and Hindustan Petroleum Corporation (HPCL) today paid an interim dividend of Rs 582.84 crore to the government for the fiscal 2003-04.																								 Mumbai, Jan. 7: Promoters of CLC Global Group, Mukund Chowdhury and associates, have acquired the 48.87 per cent stake held by RPG Enterprises in Spentex Industries. 
